:alias_controls
    SecuDE Tool 2.1   Alias Services

This subtool of SecTool provides comfortable
alias editing functions.

User aliases can be installed, changed, and
deleted, System aliases can be displayed.

SecTool takes care of save access to alias 
files (it's not advisable to edit them directly)
and performs several consistency checks. 
# 
:alias_type_setting
Alias type setting:

 - Select one of four possible alias types
   which is displayed in the alias list
 - If type is not available in the selected
   alias file (User/System/both), the alias
   output is "???"
 - If both files are selected, User's aliases
   are printed prior to System aliases in alias
   list

# 
:alias_file_setting
Alias File setting:

 - User's own aliases
 - System aliases (not editable)
 - or both

 - All lines in alias list are marked with an
   small image to notifiy their DName's origin


# 
:alias_find_button
Alias Find button:

 - Pattern string taken from alias clipboard is
   searched in any alias entry's DName and alias
   string
 - Comparisons are non-case-sensitive
 - On success, the entry is selected and 
   displayed (if entry's origination file is not
   the actual one, switch setting)
 - Find next and find top down is available

# 
:alias_list
Alias list:

 - Show User/System-aliases to DNames
 - DNames are sorted in alphabetical order
 - If an alias list entry is selected (via mouse
   click), its DName's set of aliases is
   displayed, and editing functions are allowed

   

# 
:alias_names_button
Alias Names button:

 - Install extra aliases that are needed along 
   with the three standard types
 - An alias given in alias name textfield is
   appended to entry's aliases (with lowest
   priority) via mouse click on menu button
   or choice <Insert> in button's menu.
 - Extra aliases are listed in button's menu
 - Changes are made to User's entries only
 - If DName has no entry in User's file,
   insert installs DName
 - Extra aliases are taken for missing standard
   aliases, they don't appear in menu's list
 - Changes take place directly (i.e. Change
   button must not be activated)

# 
:alias_apply_button
Alias Apply button:

 - All changed data are saved to User's alias
   file (Remember: System's alias file is 
   read-only)
 - Changes of alias list are notified by
   "Save needed" in the window's right bottom
   corner

# 
:alias_reset_button
Alias Reset button:

 - Alias list is read again from files

# 
:alias_add_button
Alias Add button:

 - New DName with at least one guilty alias,
   all taken from the textfields, is added to 
   alias list
 - If a System entry is selected, Add copies
   DName and alias to User's entries

# 
:alias_change_button
Alias Change button:

 - Accept changes of User's Local name, Internet 
   Mail, and X.400 Mail aliases for DName, all
   taken from the textfields

 - Notice: Extra names are dealed with Name list
   button

# 
:alias_delete_button
Alias Delete button:

 - Selected DName entry and its aliases are 
   removed from alias list (User's entry only)

